params.name: do_resize
params.description: Whether to resize the images (height, width) dimensions. Can be overidden by do_resize in preprocess.

params.name: size
params.type: Dict[str, int] optional, defaults to {"height" -- 384, "width": 384}):Size of the image after resizing. Can be overidden by size in preprocess.

params.name: resample
params.description: Defines the resampling filter to use if resizing the image. Can be overidden by resample in preprocess.

params.name: keep_aspect_ratio
params.description: If True, the image is resized to the largest possible size such that the aspect ratio is preserved. Canbe overidden by keep_aspect_ratio in preprocess.

params.name: ensure_multiple_of
params.description: If do_resize is True, the image is resized to a size that is a multiple of this value. Can be overiddenby ensure_multiple_of in preprocess.

params.name: do_rescale
params.description: Whether to rescale the image by the specified scale rescale_factor. Can be overidden by do_rescale inpreprocess.

params.name: rescale_factor
params.description: Scale factor to use if rescaling the image. Can be overidden by rescale_factor in preprocess.

params.name: do_normalize
params.description: Whether to normalize the image. Can be overridden by the do_normalize parameter in the preprocessmethod.

params.name: image_mean
params.description: Mean to use if normalizing the image. This is a float or list of floats the length of the number ofchannels in the image. Can be overridden by the image_mean parameter in the preprocess method.

params.name: image_std
params.description: Standard deviation to use if normalizing the image. This is a float or list of floats the length of thenumber of channels in the image. Can be overridden by the image_std parameter in the preprocess method.

params.name: do_pad
params.description: Whether to apply center padding. This was introduced in the DINOv2 paper, which uses the model incombination with DPT.

params.name: size_divisor
params.description: If do_pad is True, pads the image dimensions to be divisible by this value. This was introduced in theDINOv2 paper, which uses the model in combination with DPT.

params.name: prompt_scale_to_meter
params.description: Scale factor to convert the prompt depth to meters.
